PG| ***** 27 ***** |


ht|j|at|^M@2^Z@3Other people play it shows both unbid suits. Therefore, if the auction goes,|
PG| ***** 28 ***** |


HT|k|AT|^B{|ia|1s2c2sd|at|}|HT|m|at|the double would mean hearts and diamonds. |
PG| ***** 29 ***** |


HT|o|at|^B@2Personally, I am not a big fan of responsive doubles. I think they are confusing and they are not universally accepted as to when a double is responsive and what it shows. So, if you decide you want to play them, it needs partnership discussion. Further, they are definitely alertable.|
PG| ***** 30 ***** |


AT|

In conclusion, if you decide to play them, my recommendation is that a double is responsive if there are two suits remaining, and that the double shows both other suits. The point requirements are the same as negative doubles, perhaps a bit more, since the overcaller need not have an opening hand.|
