^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Let me quckly go over the responses to 4N with a void. If you have an even number of key cards and a useful void, you can bid 5N. If you have one or three key cards and a useful void, you bid the suit you are void in, assuming it is lower than the key card suit. Let us say hearts are trump. If it goes 4N and you respond 5N, that shows an even number of key cards and an unspecified void. If it goes 4N and you respond 6C or 6D that shows an odd number of key cards and a club or diamond void. And if you respond 6H, that shows a spade void (you can't jump past 6H). |
