hondo717: Let's talk a little about the bidding. First of all, you should agree on whether or not you open 1 of a major or 1N with a balanced 15-17 and a 5 card major.  I recommend opening 1N, because otherwise it is hard to show your points. Hands with 15-17 are often hard to show, because they are too weak for a jump shift, but more than a min. However, assuming you open those hands 1 of a major, then D's 2NT bid gives K multiple choices. It says first of all choose between NT and hearts. With K's hand I would have chosen NT because of the flat distribution. It also says, bid game with 8 or 9, either hearts or 3NT. So, I would have passed with K's hand, since he has a min, and three Hearts the a bid 3@H is reasonable. It just says he has a min and prefers hearts.|
